  "notes": "Modern Israeli Hebrew. Consonantal abjad — vowel diacritics (niqqud) normally omitted in adult text. Bgdkpt rule: ב/כ/פ = stops after consonant or word-initially, fricatives elsewhere. ר = /ʁ/ in most Israeli speech. ח and כ (final) both = /χ/. ע and א are /ʔ/ or silent in colloquial speech. Dagesh lene distinguishes stop vs. fricative in ב,כ,פ.",
