    "stress_mark": "ˈ",
    "notes": "Modern Israeli Hebrew default is milra (final stress, -1). Milel (penultimate) is common in a substantial minority of words (especially segolate nouns: מֶלֶךְ, שֶׁמֶשׁ) and cannot be predicted from unvocalized orthography. With niqqud the stressed syllable is identifiable; without niqqud (the norm in adult text) stress placement is not reliably computable from orthography alone. This block models the milra default only. Source: Bolozky (1997)."
  },
